---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
// NOTE FOR LAUNCH: this is a genuine draft privacy notice, not legal advice.
// Have it reviewed/approved by whoever handles TMC's data protection, and
// confirm: the privacy contact address, ICO registration number (if any),
// and retention periods, before go-live.
const lastUpdated = 'July 2026';
const contactEmail = 'wellbeing@themoleclinic.co.uk';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How The Mole Clinic collects and uses your data when you create a CPD account."
>
  <section class="bg-tmc-primary text-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-14">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-light text-white mb-3">Privacy notice</h1>
      <p class="text-tmc-light/80 text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 text-tmc-text leading-relaxed">
      <p class="mb-6">
        This notice explains how The Mole Clinic ("we", "us") collects and uses your
        personal data when you create an account for our skin cancer CPD programme, and
        your rights under UK data protection law (UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018).
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-tmc-primary mt-8 mb-3">Who we are</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        The data controller is The Mole Clinic (<a href="https://themoleclinic.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-tmc-accent hover:text-tmc-primary underline underline-offset-2">themoleclinic.co.uk</a>).
        For any privacy question or to exercise your rights, contact us at{' '}
        <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`} class="text-tmc-accent hover:text-tmc-primary underline underline-offset-2">{contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-tmc-primary mt-8 mb-3">What we collect</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 space-y-1">
        <li>Your email address (to create your account and sign you in)</li>
        <li>Your profession, and optionally your workplace and HCPC registration number</li>
        <li>Your name, if you provide it</li>
        <li>Your progress through the CPD modules (which modules you have completed)</li>
        <li>Whether you have consented to marketing contact, and when</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-tmc-primary mt-8 mb-3">Why we use it, and our lawful basis</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 space-y-1">
        <li><span class="font-medium">To provide the CPD programme</span> (account, sign-in, tracking your completion and issuing certification) — lawful basis: performance of a contract / taking steps at your request.</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium">To email you about the CPD programme and related updates</span> — lawful basis: your consent, given by ticking the consent box. You can withdraw this at any time (see your rights below).</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium">To keep the service secure and working</span> — lawful basis: our legitimate interests in operating a reliable, secure service.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-tmc-primary mt-8 mb-3">Who we share it with</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">We do not sell your data. We use the following processors to run the service, who process your data only on our instructions:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 space-y-1">
        <li><span class="font-medium">Supabase</span> — accounts, authentication and database (hosted in the EU/UK region)</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium">Resend</span> — sending sign-in and confirmation emails</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium">Microsoft Azure</span> — secure storage and delivery of the course videos (UK region)</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium">Netlify</span> — hosting of the website</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Some of these providers may process data outside the UK. Where they do, appropriate
        safeguards (such as the UK International Data Transfer Agreement or equivalent
        standard contractual clauses) are in place.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-tmc-primary mt-8 mb-3">How long we keep it</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        We keep your account and CPD records for as long as you have an account with us, and
        for a reasonable period afterwards so you can retrieve your CPD evidence. If you ask
        us to delete your account, we will do so, subject to any records we must retain by law.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-tmc-primary mt-8 mb-3">Your rights</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Under UK data protection law you have the right to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 space-y-1">
        <li>access the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>ask us to correct inaccurate data</li>
        <li>ask us to delete your data</li>
        <li>object to, or ask us to restrict, certain processing</li>
        <li>withdraw your consent to marketing at any time — by using the unsubscribe link in any email, or by contacting us</li>
        <li>data portability</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-6">
        To exercise any of these, email{' '}
        <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`} class="text-tmc-accent hover:text-tmc-primary underline underline-offset-2">{contactEmail}</a>.
        If you are unhappy with how we handle your data, you can complain to the Information
        Commissioner's Office (ICO) at{' '}
        <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-tmc-accent hover:text-tmc-primary underline underline-offset-2">ico.org.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-tmc-primary mt-8 mb-3">Cookies</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        We use only the strictly necessary cookies required to keep you signed in. We do not
        use advertising or third-party tracking cookies.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-tmc-primary mt-8 mb-3">Changes to this notice</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        We may update this notice from time to time. The date at the top shows when it was
        last changed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
